article.description: Baron's 29 lead Canisius to 85-83 win over Iona
article.headline: Baron's 29 lead Canisius to 85-83 win over Iona
article.linkText: Baron's 29 lead Canisius to 85-83 win over Iona
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Billy Baron scored 29 points and Canisius squandered a 20-point lead on Friday night, but battled past Iona 85-83. Iona had the ball with 18 seconds left and the scored tied at 83 when Baron intercepted a careless pass over the middle, drove the length of the court and drew a foul on his attempted layup. Baron made both free throws, and Sean Armand missed a last-second attempt to win the game for Iona with a 3-pointer. Baron also had eight assists and eclipsed 1,000 points during his Canisius career. Canisius (12-6, 6-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) built its biggest lead at 61-41 before Iona rattled off 11 straight points. The Griffins built their lead back to 15, and then Iona went on an 18-0 run to go in front 74-71. Armand led Iona (8-8, 5-2) with 19 points with A.J. English and Isaiah Williams adding 18 and 17, respectively.
